Note: ============================================================================
Note: Source-Level Translation Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
End-to-end source convenience entry for the COBOL frontend, mirroring the
python_to_hir_from_source contract: it owns the full parse + lower pipeline
so the central translation dispatcher can route COBOL source text straight
to a HIR root with a single call. Unlike the borrow-the-lexer frontends,
the COBOL parser owns its pipeline end to end: parse_cobol(source)
internally allocates its own scan arena, constructs the COBOL lexer and
parser from the source, walks all four divisions
(IDENTIFICATION/ENVIRONMENT/DATA/PROCEDURE) to a COBOL_PROGRAM AST, and
tears down its lexer and parser before returning - the AST nodes and their
lexeme handles are heap-allocated independently and outlive that internal
parser. So this wrapper does not manage any lexer or parser lifetime; it
only owns the translation arena that translate_cobol_to_hir needs for its
HIR allocations. A 65536-byte translation arena is allocated here and
handed to the lowering pass; the resulting HIR lives in that arena and is
independent of the parse-time state. Returning 0 on null source,
arena-allocation failure, or parse failure matches Runa's nullable-pointer
convention and the dispatcher's documented error convention (a 0 return is
treated as "frontend failed").
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Null-guard source (return 0). Allocate a 65536-byte translation arena for
the HIR lowering; return 0 on failure. parse_cobol(source) builds its own
lexer/parser/scan-arena internally and walks the COBOL divisions to a
COBOL_PROGRAM AST root, releasing its internal parser before returning; on
a 0 root return 0. Lower the AST with translate_cobol_to_hir(ast, arena),
capturing the HIR root, and return it.
@End Implementation
Process called "cobol_to_hir_from_source" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let arena be proc allocate from Layout with 65536
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ast be proc parse_cobol from Parser with source
    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir be proc translate_cobol_to_hir with ast, arena

    Return hir
End Process

Note: End of COBOL to HIR Translator
